<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">ACU 213</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">English Language Course For Erasmus I</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Reading Skill-At the end of this course, students will be able to
• read for/understand specific information, main ideas, gist and opinions
• Use pre-reading skills to activate schemata and predict content of advanced texts
• identify the common types of support in arguments, their relevance and irrelevance, common argument flaws, opposing points of views and refutations
• expand targeted vocabulary</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Discussion
Vocabulary Study</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Complete IELTS Cambridge</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=413798&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
